@jilsander Pre-Fall 2026 campaign is putting the spotlight on an unexpected cast: the clothes themselves. Photographed by Blommers & Schumm, the campaign pairs portraits of five models with a series of character studies that imagine key pieces from Simone Bellotti’s latest collection as personalities of their own.⁠
⁠
From a long overcoat awkwardly propping itself up to a pair of Hood moccasins balancing on tiptoe, each garment takes on a distinct mood and presence. It’s a fitting reflection of Bellotti’s evolving vision for Jil Sander, where quiet, refined designs reveal their individuality through closer inspection.⁠

@prada Spring/Summer 2027 menswear show put climbing gear in the luxury spotlight.⁠ ⁠ From reworked monk strap shoes with mountaineering-inspired details to mini chalk bags transformed into clip-on Prada accessories, the collection’s biggest talking points came off the rock wall.⁠ ⁠
⁠
Positioned as an “antidote to complication,” *Clarity* reflects fashion’s growing obsession with performance wear, proving once again that few brands can make technical gear feel quite as desirable as Prada.⁠

@JulienDossena lascia @Rabanne. Direttore creativo dal 2014, ha riportato la maison dei Sixties al centro del discorso contemporaneo: il rilancio della maglia metallica nel 2017, la prima collezione maschile nel 2019, l’apertura al beauty e la collaborazione con H&M. Undici anni di radicalità e movimento si chiudono oggi, Il suo prossimo capitolo potrebbe essere da Alaïa. Continua a leggere l’articolo a cura di @AlessandroViapiana_.
Photo: Getty Images
#JulienDossena #Rabanne #Fashion

