Jordyn Woods's orange bag has been credited with bringing the Knicks its first NBA Championship final win in 53 years. It has been blessed by New York City’s mayor, Zohran Mamdani. It even enjoyed the VIP treatment at a celebratory parade. It is now going to be exhibited at the Guggenheim Museum.
@jordynwoods, who is engaged to the Knicks center @karltowns, wore the leather clutch to all but one of the games in the lead up to the finals. On the days she brought the bag, which is from her own label, Woods by Jordyn, the Knicks won. (The day the team broke its winning streak was, coincidentally, the day that Madison Square Garden implemented a strict no-bag policy and heightened security for President Trump’s attendance.)
“This bag came to represent a cultural moment,” Mariët Westermann, the director of the Guggenheim, said. Tap the link in our bio to read more about the purse’s urban legend. Photos by The Hapa Blonde/GC Images, via Getty Images, Jordyn Woods

